# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# gpth (Google Photos Takeout Helper) is the **Dart-
# based Google Photos Takeout organizer** by
# TheLastGimbus — restructures the chaotic Google
# Photos Takeout zip into a clean year/month folder
# tree with album organization.  Pivots from Scala
# decline (R278 fs2chat-client) into the **Dart
# language tooling cluster**.  Sister to flutter-cli
# / dart-cli / pub (Dart's package manager).  **MAJOR
# MILESTONE**: corpus's **first documented Dart CLI**
# AND first use of the **Dart args package** — adds
# Dart to the cross-language CLI taxonomy (18 library
# variants now).
#
# Critical extraction note: gpth uses **Dart's
# `package:args/args.dart`** library — corpus's
# **first documented Dart CLI** AND first use of the
# **Dart args package**.  `args` is **the** standard
# Dart CLI library — maintained by the Dart team
# itself.  Used by Dart's own `dart` CLI tool, pub,
# flutter, build_runner, and most Dart/Flutter
# tooling.  Extends the **cross-language CLI taxonomy**
# to EIGHTEEN library variants (R276 added Java
# picocli; R277 added Kotlin clikt; R278 added Scala
# decline; R279 adds Dart args): Rust (6), Go (4),
# Python (3), Crystal, Haskell, OCaml, C, Java
# picocli, Kotlin clikt, Scala decline, **Dart args**
# (R279 — NEW).  Documents the **Dart args builder-
# pattern with cascade operator**:
# ```dart
#   final parser = ArgParser()
#     ..addFlag('help', abbr: 'h', negatable: false)
#     ..addOption('input', abbr: 'i', help: '...')
#     ..addOption('albums', allowed: [...], defaultsTo: 'shortcut');
# ```
# Distinct from picocli's annotations (R276 Java) and
# clikt's by-delegation (R277 Kotlin) and decline's
# applicative composition (R278 Scala).
#
# Critical extraction note: gpth uses **Dart cascade
# operator `..`** at gpth.dart:30-64 — Dart's
# `expression..methodCall()` syntax invokes
# `methodCall()` on `expression` but returns
# `expression` itself (not the result of methodCall).
# This makes chained method calls possible WITHOUT
# the method returning `this` (unlike Rust builder
# patterns or Kotlin .apply).  Documents the **Dart
# cascade operator** — a language-level feature
# distinct from builder-style fluent chaining in
# other languages.  Used pervasively for object
# initialization in Dart.  Equivalent in spirit to
# Kotlin's `apply { }` scope function and to method-
# returning-this builder patterns in Rust/Java, but
# operates AT THE LANGUAGE LEVEL.  Corpus's **first
# documented Dart cascade operator usage**.
#
# Critical extraction note: gpth uses **auto-negatable
# flags with `negatable: false` opt-out** at
# gpth.dart:30 — Dart args **AUTO-GENERATES `--no-FLAG`
# form for every boolean flag UNLESS `negatable: false`
# is set**.  For example, `addFlag('cache-result',
# help: '...')` automatically creates BOTH `--cache-
# result` and `--no-cache-result` flags.  `addFlag
# ('help', abbr: 'h', negatable: false)` disables the
# auto `--no-help` generation.  Documents the **auto-
# negatable flag pattern** in Dart args.  Distinct
# from Click's `--FLAG/--no-FLAG` PAIRED syntax
# (R266 uvicorn) which requires explicit slash-syntax
# declaration — Dart's approach is OPT-OUT (default
# is auto-generate the `--no-X` form for every flag).
# Corpus's **first documented auto-negatable opt-out
# pattern** — a Dart-specific default-behavior
# choice.
#
# Critical extraction note: gpth uses
# **`addOption('albums', allowed: [...], allowedHelp:
# {...}, defaultsTo: '...')`** at gpth.dart:45-51 —
# restricted-values option API in Dart args.
# `allowed` accepts an `Iterable<String>` of valid
# values; `allowedHelp` accepts a `Map<String, String>`
# of per-value descriptions; `defaultsTo` sets the
# default.  When `--help` is shown, the per-value
# descriptions are rendered in a sub-section under
# the option's help.  Documents the **Dart args
# restricted-values API** — distinct from clap's
# `value_parser = [...]` (R209 slice), Click's
# `click.Choice([...])` (R266 uvicorn), and clikt's
# `choice("a", "b")` (R277).  Dart's approach uniquely
# supports **per-value help descriptions** alongside
# the allowed list — useful when each enum value has
# a distinct semantic.  Plus the `allowed` parameter
# can take a Map's `.keys` (Iterable) — convenient
# when the allowed values are derived from another
# data structure.  Corpus's **first documented
# allowed + allowedHelp paired API**.
#
# Critical extraction note: gpth uses **`parser.parse
# (arguments)` returning `ArgResults`** at
# gpth.dart:67 — Dart args's parse method returns an
# `ArgResults` object that's queried via `res[key]`
# subscript syntax and iterated via `res.options`
# (Iterable of parsed flag names).  Plus `res
# .arguments` returns the leftover positional args
# (not consumed by flags).  Documents the **Dart
# ArgResults dynamic-map pattern** — similar to
# Python argparse's Namespace (R267 alembic) but
# returned as an iterable-map rather than an
# attribute object.  Distinct from clap derive's
# typed struct fields (R247+).  Useful for dynamic
# arg handling without typed structs.
#
# Critical extraction note: gpth uses **stdin-as-TTY
# detection** at gpth.dart:72 — `stdin.hasTerminal`
# checks if stdin is a TTY (interactive terminal).
# Used to auto-enable interactive mode when no args
# are provided AND stdin is a terminal.  Documents
# the **`stdin.hasTerminal` Dart pattern** — same
# convergent design pattern as R273 irust + R274
# koto (both Rust) which use `stdin.is_tty()`.
# Pattern now documented in **3 corpus rounds across
# 2 languages**: irust (Rust), koto (Rust), gpth
# (Dart).  Strongly confirms this is the idiomatic
# Unix-tool pattern for "stdin pipe-mode detection".
# Convergent design across languages.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line

# 4 album option values from
# lib/interactive.dart:23-33.
local -a album_options=(
  'shortcut:[Recommended] album folders with symlinks/shortcuts to year-photos'
  'duplicate-copy:album folders with photos copied into them'
  'json:put ALL photos in one folder + .json with album info'
  'nothing:ignore albums; put year-photos into one folder'
)

# 10 flags/options decoded source-direct from gpth.dart
# lines 30-64.  Dart args AUTO-GENERATES `--no-FLAG`
# form for boolean flags (negatable=true default).
_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help (negatable: false; no --no-help auto-generated)]' \
  '--fix=[folder with photos to fix dates (skips Takeout procedure)]:dir:_files -/' \
  '--interactive[use interactive mode]' \
  '--no-interactive[disable interactive mode (auto-generated by Dart args)]' \
  '(-i --input)'{-i+,--input=}'[input folder with all takeouts extracted]:dir:_files -/' \
  '(-o --output)'{-o+,--output=}'[output folder for organized photos]:dir:_files -/' \
  '--albums=[what to do about albums (default: shortcut)]:strategy:(($album_options))' \
  '--divide-to-dates[divide output into year/month folders]' \
  '--no-divide-to-dates[do NOT divide output by date (auto-generated)]' \
  '--skip-extras[skip extra images like -edited variants]' \
  '--no-skip-extras[include extras (auto-generated)]' \
  '--guess-from-name[try to guess file dates from names (default: true)]' \
  '--no-guess-from-name[disable name-based date guessing]' \
  '--copy[copy files instead of moving (slower; preserves input folder)]' \
  '--no-copy[move files (default; auto-generated)]'
